public class GXLEdge
extends GXLLocalConnection

Represents the GXL edge element.

The edge element represents a binary edge between two graph elements.

Children
GXLType - see GXLType.
GXLAttr - Attributes describing this edge.
GXLGraph - edge elements may contain graph elements, creating a hierarchical graph.

Attributes
id - Optional id of this edge element.
from - Required id referencing the source graph element of this edge.
to - Required id referencing the target graph element of this edge.
fromorder - Optional integer that describes an ordering of the incident tentacles of the source element.
toorder - Optional integer that describes an ordering of the incident tentacles of the target element.
isdirected - Optional boolean defining if this edge is directed. Note that this attribute overrides the edgemode attribute of the wrapping graph element (see GXLGraph).

See Also:
GXLLocalConnection, GXLRel, GXLGraphElement

Constructor Detail

GXLEdge

public GXLEdge(GXLGraphElement source,
               GXLGraphElement target)
Creates a new GXLEdge element with the specified source and target. Note that only the ids of the graph elements are stored and that changing these ids prior to adding the elements to a GXLDocument will result in this being a dangling edge (since it can't find the source or target). Once both the edge, source and target is part of a document, any id changes will ripple through to the edge. Note also, from the same reason, that both the source and the target MUST have their ids set.

Parameters:
source - The graph element that is the source of this edge.
target - The graph element that is the target of this edge.

getSource

public GXLGraphElement getSource()
Returns the graph element that is the source of this edge, or null if this is a dangling edge. Note that all edges that is not a part of a GXLDocument is automatically dangling, otherwise a null result of this method means that the GXLDocument that this edge belongs to doesn't contain an element with the id specified by this edge as it's source.

Returns:
The graph element that is the source of this edge, or null if this is a dangling edge.

Whether this edge's source tentacle is ordered relative to the source.

getSourceIncidenceOrder

public int getSourceIncidenceOrder()
Returns the integer used to order this edge's source tentacle relative to the source's other incident tentacles. Note that the value returned from this method is only valid if the method hasSourceIncidenceOrder() returns true. This method is mostly a shorthand for getAttribute(GXL.FROMORDER) albeit the String is converted to an integer first.

Returns:
The integer used to order this edge's source tentacle relative to the source's other incident tentacles.

setSourceIncidenceOrder

public void setSourceIncidenceOrder(int order)
Sets the integer used to order this edge's source tentacle relative to the source's other incident tentacles. Note that the value of order must be unique to all the tentacles incident to the source. This method is a shorthand for setAttribute(GXL.FROMORDER, String.valueOf(order))

Parameters:
order - The integer to be used to order this edge's source tentacle relative to the source's other incident tentacles.
Throws:
GXLValidationException - If this action would result in an invalid GXL document.
